<br>
(after 20th lvl) Hail Weltria Ostriss (she BOW'd to me!) on the 3rd flr of the Erudin Library. Listen to the story of escaped citizens, request to obtain collection of scrolls. Upon accepting the quest, you recieve an 8-slot large scroll case (lore, no drop, w/combine) and run off to the dungeon! nope... bad idea. wait until at least 24th... target is still blue and only the leaders and elders will jump you (heh! small comfort).<br>
<br>
Target is Lore keeper Roggick, a 22nd shammy, that spawns in a room on the right-side of the throneroom. He will usually be carrying 1 scroll, sometimes 2, many times 0.<br>
The difficult part (other than stayin alive) is you need 8 different scrolls. I currently have 7 and 32 copies of those 7. Written in Elder Teir'Dal my list is as follows by frequency of drop.<br>
  1. The Fall of Kolbok<br>
  2. The Arrival of Rallos Zek<br>
  3. Kobolds in the Age of Scale<br>
  4. Kobold Age of Blood<br>
  5. The Council and the Dwarves<br>
  6. The Rise of King Gkar and Clan Kolbok<br>
  7. The Ascension of Rolfron Zek<br>
  8. ?<br>
<br>
 Now to how Im doing this (mind you, its not flawless... 3 deaths since implementing it). With sheilds, lev and invis up, I followed another group into the throneroom and quickly ran to the far back rt.side corner, where you can sit/med and BIND. To your right now is the throne (King Gragnor, 25th SK. and H.Shaman Drogik, 23rd). To the left is a door to the target. With invis up you can safely run in and setup in corner and hit him with a bolt then shock away! Only concern is if a pack elder wanders in, he will join the fight (root, move back to other corner). Once target is secured, port out to Tox or NK whatever. ID your scroll(s), wait an hour. Gate back, pop'im again, port out.<br>
<br>
 /apologize for length.<br>
<br>
 On to some questions...<br>
Ive tagged this dog close to 50 times now. Are there other known quests of a comparable nature of diff/lvl/etc. that could suggest what the reward for this might be?<br>
<br>
 Could someone on Inny that can read Elder TD, take screenshots of the scrolls, and get them here to Graffe's? /waves to Fasty...<br>
<br>
 Good Huntin all!  Yahtzooba <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/useverinewolfe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Severine Wolfe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/13/01 8:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lorekeeper Roggik</span><hr size=1> I am assuming that the dungeon you speak of is The Warrens.  I am too high in level to hunt there so I have not done this quest, since it was obviously activated when the Warrens opened and I was too high then to hunt there.  I did scout there with my wiz so that my Ranger could navigate there.  The pathing is this dungeon is about the worst I've seen so I would suggest that young wizards do anything in there with extreme caution.<br>
<br>
I wish you luck, friend. <p>Severine <BR>
